<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-887-840  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 887 840.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Modern Office Technology  Nov 1989 v34 n11 p18(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CAR saves time, adds security. (University of North Texas usesEastman Kodak's KAR records-management system)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The University of North Texas installed Eastman-Kodak's KARinformation system to keep pace with enrollment growth withoutincreasing staff by automating document storage and retrieval.andO;KAR was chosen because it could solve the school's immediaterecords-management problems and could keep pace with futurerecord-keeping needs at the school.andP;  The security of studentrecords is improved by the system, according to Registrar JoneelHarris, because microfilm originals can be stored off-site; Harrisclaims records preparation is much faster because operators neednot organize documents in social security order and cut and insertfilmed documents as they had to previously with the microfichejacket system.andP;  Almost 10,000 documents a month are microfilmed ona Kodak Starfile RV-3 planetary camera; other data is downloadedinto the KAR system from the school's mainframe computer.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Ticker:    EK.andO;Product:   Kodak KAR (Information retrieval system) (usage).andO;Topic:     Colleges and UniversitiesRecords ManagementAutomationInformation Storage and RetrievalApplicationsNorth Texas State University.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>